Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.36,0:00:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.94,0:00:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we played classical music\Nto our shiitake mushrooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.86,0:00:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they grew positively huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.36,0:00:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? You don't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hit them with electricity,\Nlike artificial lightning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.53,0:00:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they grow even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.41,0:00:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Electricity?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.45,0:00:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. When they're stimulated\Nby a strong current,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.83,0:00:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,mushroom fungal filaments\Nfeel a sense of danger,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and apparently actively grow\Nbigger to ensure they reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever, just do your homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.74,0:00:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A helicopter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.58,0:01:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.54,0:01:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi liked helicopters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.97,0:01:26.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You hold your breath to make it through\Nthe bewildering day that confronts you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.81,0:01:32.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what this is, don't you?\NWhat do you want to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.98,0:01:39.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The pain from shrugging\Nit all off as nothing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.57,0:01:45.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}urges you on enough to be encouraging{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:52.13,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Catching hold but making a mess,\Nwe're still inadequate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.13,0:02:00.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as long as we can forge\Nour shining, unseen future selves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:08.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Awaken and run where it takes you,\Nleaving mirages behind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:15.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run with your desire to change,\Nfrom your comfort zone into freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:22.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Start choosing between now\Nand the brilliance you can attain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:30.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unaware of your destination,\Ndeep breaths following shallow ones{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.26,0:02:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi-{\i1}san{\i0}? Do you mean Ogi\NTakahiro-{\i1}san{\i0}, of Class 2-B?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.55,0:02:42.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Mountain Range Clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.05,0:02:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the one in Class 2-B.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an Ogi you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was our English teacher\Nin middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.48,0:02:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, {\i1}that {\i0}one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I know Ogi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}.\NBut I didn't know he liked helicopters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.15,0:03:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Ogi's liking of\Nhelicopters was well-known.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.15,0:03:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara, you knew, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. How is it that\NI know about it, but they don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They both went to\NKaburaya Middle School, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.25,0:03:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Ibara and I were\Nalways in the same class.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way she wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.59,0:03:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, is there something\Nthe matter over this Ogi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara, you remember, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, a helicopter flew over\NKaburaya Middle School, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, several dozen times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.06,0:03:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about just one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.77,0:03:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle of class,\NOgi suddenly ran to the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looked up into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.48,0:03:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He kept watching as the helicopter\Nflew off into the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then said something about\Nhow he liked helicopters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to laugh it off, before\Ngetting back to class, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, when you add in all\Nthose details, I do remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That did happen. Was that Ogi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.33,0:03:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was Ogi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's better. I wasn't misremembering it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.34,0:04:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange or not, that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.80,0:04:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when JSDF helicopters\Nfly around in squadrons,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.72,0:04:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's quite a sight to see, and yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.10,0:04:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember Ogi-{\i1}sensei\N{\i0}ever reacting to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.94,0:04:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's a "squadron"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you tell they were JSDF?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.53,0:04:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I can't think of\Nany other helicopter groups
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that fly around in formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're sure that Ogi was\Naround when that would happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.62,0:04:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do remember seeing those helicopters
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looking up the word "AGM"\Nin my English dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.25,0:04:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AGM?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.59,0:04:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An abbreviation for\N"air-to-ground missile."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.34,0:04:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right; if those were to fly over,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.01,0:04:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi would probably run out onto\Nthe school grounds and dance around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.05,0:04:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt he would actually dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.60,0:04:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, it was Ogi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}that\Nwas thrilled by helicopters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like it was just after we\Nstarted going to middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\NI seem to remember thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There sure are some strange\Nteachers in middle school."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.53,0:05:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, like Fuku-{\i1}chan {\i0}mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never saw Ogi reacting\Nto helicopters after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago, huh?\NMy memories have grown fuzzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.79,0:05:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now that she mentions it,\Nexcept for that one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember Ogi doing similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you mention Ogi-{\i1}sensei{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.76,0:05:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's another legend that\Nhas a major impact, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.72,0:05:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An astounding legend concerning Ogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go making your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.64,0:05:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that. This isn't one I made.\NOgi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}himself said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Ogi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}... I kind of\Nfind it hard to believe, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure you'll\Nbelieve me when I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not saying it's\Nimpossible either, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.33,0:05:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and spill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.41,0:05:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Ogi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he has been struck by lightning\Nthree times in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.04,0:06:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! By lightning, you mean {\i1}lightning{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. As in "thunder!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.51,0:06:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three times? I'm surprised he's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.80,0:06:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was struck by it... {\i1}sandodaa{\i0}!\N[{\i1}sandodaa{\i0}: three times/thunder]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three times? I'm surprised he's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.81,0:06:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like Chitanda has\Nfigured out how to deal with Satoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it didn't hit him directly,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but even so, he didn't get away unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.49,0:06:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was knocked\Nunconscious once,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he has some burn marks on his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right? But he is still alive,\Nso that's one consolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.37,0:06:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.67,0:06:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he didn't\Nhave any scars that stuck out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightning... and three times, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something like that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The city of Kamiyama doesn't\Nget all that much lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.31,0:07:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite which, Ogi alone has\Nbeen struck three times?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi doesn't seem to be lying to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth\NFalsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even said at\Nthe outset that he didn't make it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, could Ogi be lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems too incredible for it to be a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.01,0:07:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, they keep old newspapers\Nat the library, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.05,0:07:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they do. Some of them, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.68,0:07:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have some in the\Nschool library, too, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But just articles that have\Nto do with Kami High.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not going to be good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.86,0:07:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading to the library. Want to come?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:08:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, it almost looks like you're\Nmotivated about something!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.41,0:08:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I put this? I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.09,0:08:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.67,0:08:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}is {\i0}you, right, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.14,0:08:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're our energy-conservationist\NOreki Hotaro, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been taken over by an alien?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe you've been\Npossessed by Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.35,0:08:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.31,0:08:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, you should go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Warm yourself up and go right to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll be back at 100% tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.99,0:08:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude. Is it really so unusual for\Nme to do something spontaneously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever. I'll wrap this up quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.37,0:08:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're curious, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to go investigate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.42,0:08:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might not even turn anything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.05,0:08:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That there is something in this world\Nthat can tickle your curiosity!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.18,0:09:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious to know just what\Nsuch a thing might be!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.39,0:09:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's pretty rude, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi said he had homework,\Nso he wouldn't be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have helped to have Ibara,\Nthe library staffer, come along,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.15,0:09:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't have any right to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.87,0:09:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.92,0:09:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can give you a lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.03,0:09:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.78,0:09:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay. Bye, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.37,0:10:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.83,0:10:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're able to search through\Nold newspaper articles,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you check out the name\NOgi Masakiyo for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.67,0:10:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi Masakiyo is written like\N"small tree that is correct and pure."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I'll see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:28.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kanro {\i0}('Cold Dews')\NWhen the dews stiffen as they form\Nin keeping with the gray cold
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.89,0:10:28.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.12,0:10:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what my sister says,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,having gone up into the Kamikakiuchi\Nmountain range several times,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.92,0:10:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in ranges where the mountains\Nare of the 3,000-meter class,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.42,0:10:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even the air currents are blocked
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the climate can be completely\Ndifferent on the near and far sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be right to keep\NChitanda waiting for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:13.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama City Library
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found some information on Ogi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mountain trail beautification efforts\Nin the Kamikakiuchi Range."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}is someone who went\Nmountain climbing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.80,0:11:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Kamiyama Mountaineering\NAssociation began sponsoring
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,beautification efforts on the\NAbumidake mountain trail on the 26th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.97,0:11:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,11 volunteers took part,\Npicking up trash around the trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:11:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama Mountaineering Association\Ncaptain, Ogi Masakiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}, 39, said,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.15,0:12:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'The climbing boom means more climbers\Nwho don't know climbing manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.40,0:12:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like them to know that breaches\Nof manners in the mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could cost someone their life.'"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.66,0:12:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was afraid of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.71,0:12:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. Did you manage to\Nsearch all the old newspapers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, we can have them look at\Nthe counter on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of hoping this hunch\NI have doesn't prove true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, I'd like to do a\Nsearch on newspaper articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. What would you like to search?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Articles from April through May,\Nthree years ago, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:12:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any keywords?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.42,0:13:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Stranded."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.35,0:13:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are 12 hits. Would you\Nlike to narrow that down?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's all there are,\Nplease let me see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.85,0:13:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.07,0:13:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.74,0:13:30.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Search for stranded party in\NKamikakiuchi Range faces difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an article from May 9th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.24,0:13:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but could we see\Nthis newspaper article?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.75,0:13:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda sees where this is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.92,0:13:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maruta-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you have a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.88,0:13:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.67,0:13:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, we'd like to see this news article\Nfrom May 9th, three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.01,0:13:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago? Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it will take about 30 minutes\Nto get that article, is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.11,0:14:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.44,0:14:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call you over when it's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.03,0:14:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, as long as we're here,\Nwould you like to look around?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.45,0:14:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A special issue on Taira no\NKiyomorithis month, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.18,0:14:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cover is so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this feature, Taira no Kiyomori
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.68,0:14:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is presented as a child\Nof the Shirakawa-in, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.60,0:14:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is indeed that theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.78,0:14:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyajima... the Itsukashima Shrine.\NI've always wanted to go see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.28,0:14:52.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Exciting Vegetable School
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So many cabbages! The colors are so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.09,0:15:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so many tomatoes on this page!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.17,0:15:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They all look so tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.68,0:15:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we have plenty of shiitake\Nmushrooms that we harvested.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.89,0:15:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like some?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Books about insects, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.02,0:15:25.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Dung Beetles
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dung beetles, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would she choose that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.78,0:15:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, is there anything\Nyou'd like to look at?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:43.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Castles
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.59,0:15:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a huge, proper castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.13,0:15:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your house is pretty big in its own right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.97,0:15:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our house isn't {\i1}that {\i0}big.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.18,0:15:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say it's just a bit bigger than normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what standard\Nyou're using for "normal."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.03,0:16:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has been compiled within\Nthis file, so check inside here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.03,0:16:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.82,0:16:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, it's heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.76,0:16:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot in here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.39,0:16:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! It's the newspaper from May 9th!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.40,0:16:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Ogi interrupted class to\Nexpress his affection for helicopters,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was probably on this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.57,0:16:56.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Two members of Kamiyama\NMountaineering Association stranded
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in sum, what does this all mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In sum,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.46,0:17:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it wasn't the helicopters that Ogi liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.89,0:17:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi was hit by lightning three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably a true story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.43,0:17:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But would anyone in this city\Nwho works as an English teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.44,0:17:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,typically get hit by lightning so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true... they wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.61,0:17:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then it hit me. Maybe Ogi\Noften went somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that lightning {\i1}does {\i0}strike a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.08,0:17:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be the mountains, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.79,0:17:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you have a hunch it would be this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that while Ogi was a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.30,0:17:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe he was also a\Nmountain climber, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.10,0:18:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I figured it could be possible\Nand came here to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.35,0:18:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, on that day alone, did Ogi\Nlook up at the helicopter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.31,0:18:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because that helicopter had\Nsome special significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi was eagerly waiting for\Nthat helicopter to fly that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.16,0:18:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To take it a little further,\NOgi was desperately anxious
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about whether or not the\Nhelicopter would fly that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.46,0:18:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, when he heard the sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he couldn't help but check\Nto make sure what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.88,0:18:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just saying that an English teacher\Npays attention to helicopters
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.51,0:18:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't tell you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you say a mountain\Nclimber pays attention to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.93,0:18:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama here is in the shadow\Nof the Kamikakiuchi Range,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a string of 3,000-meter class mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.86,0:18:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mountain climbers in this city\Npaid attention to helicopters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.53,0:18:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might have been aerial photography,\Nor transporting materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.61,0:19:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it wasn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it wasn't...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:12.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,weather deteriorating...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.04,0:19:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A rescue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the article, it says that on\Nthe 8th, the weather was bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.63,0:19:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and helicopters were unable to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.01,0:19:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogi was worried about whether\Nthe police chopper could fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.47,0:19:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even while he was teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was anxious about the weather\Non the Kamikakiuchi Range improving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was clear on the mountain range,\Nthe helicopter would fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.98,0:19:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was clear, the stranded climbers'\Nodds of survival would improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.90,0:19:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine what kind of feelings\NOgi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}was going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell you what he was feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.29,0:19:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I think he was smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.18,0:20:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We skimmed through the\Nnewspapers for a few days after.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bodies of two stranded\Nclimbers were discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were found by the police helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.62,0:20:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.00,0:20:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.83,0:20:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay if I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.88,0:20:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you curious about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.84,0:20:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it {\i1}that {\i0}outlandish that I'd\Nvoluntarily investigate something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.10,0:20:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is. It didn't seem\Nlike something you would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.81,0:20:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's true. I usually say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.19,0:20:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do\Nsomething, I don't do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.32,0:21:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't mean it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.20,0:21:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She simply brushed aside\Nmy immutable motto.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.29,0:21:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you {\i1}do {\i0}work hard\Nfor others, in all kinds of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.46,0:21:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had you help me out\Nany number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.08,0:21:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's got it completely wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you're complacent\Nwhen it comes to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why is it that today, at least,\Nyou looked into your own question?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.35,0:21:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.01,0:21:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.93,0:21:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something I just have to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard about the\Nlightning from Satoshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.32,0:21:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it evoked an unpleasant\Nassociation in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you mentioned that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.61,0:21:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to make it clear whether\NI was right about it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I decided to go investigate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.95,0:21:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I went to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:21:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it had been some major investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.00,0:21:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would keep me there a whole week,\Nthen that's another matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.34,0:22:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if it only meant flipping through\Nold newspapers, no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.30,0:22:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had you to help, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.34,0:22:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it were true, it was something\NI should be careful about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.80,0:22:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.39,0:22:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, with\Neverything that happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.19,0:22:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't just casually say\N"Ogi sure likes helicopters, huh?"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.61,0:22:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be insensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.32,0:22:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's something that\NI try to be careful about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.24,0:22:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that too hard for her to follow?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.83,0:22:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe not insensitive, but, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.17,0:22:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that feeling of "not knowing\Nhow the other guy feels."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.59,0:22:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll probably never run into Ogi again,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so maybe how he feels\Nisn't a major concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.43,0:22:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.51,0:22:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.02,0:22:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... very...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.02,0:23:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't really express it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.86,0:23:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was she trying to say? Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.32,0:23:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she can't express it well,\NI won't be able to get it out of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.37,0:23:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, gotta go. Thanks for\Nhelping me out today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.37,0:23:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.25,0:23:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I got to see such an\Nunexpected side of you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.59,0:23:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.30,0:23:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.89,0:23:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.90,0:23:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the time Chitanda gets home,\Nnight will have fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.61,0:23:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda's the one who\Noffered to tag along.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.40,0:23:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I asked her\Nto come. Then again...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.70,0:23:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I do owe her one for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:23.27,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This situation is an unscientific\Nmontage of emotions{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.90,0:24:26.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is calling whom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.57,0:24:32.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your gaze darts away when I turn around\N(I can feel it){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.53,0:24:34.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's unkind to tell me I'm imagining things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.78,0:24:40.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They say having antennas\Nis a talent, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.29,0:24:45.42,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean I want to know\N(I mean) (don't you?){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.42,0:24:52.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll turn up the heat on your youth\Nfor you now, while there's time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.17,0:24:56.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can solve this tomorrow,\Nwhy not solve it right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.85,0:25:02.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to solve your mystery{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.43,0:25:07.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Track down that secretive boyish figure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.15,0:25:14.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Today) you are a fantasy,\Ndrawing me to you, no fair!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.70,0:25:20.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My curiosity is expanding,\Nlack of tricks notwithstanding{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.37,0:25:27.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fascinated, and I have to know, why?{\i0}
